post_text:
GREAT NEWS FROM IGS!!!!!!!!!!

Iuka Grade School has been approved to participate in the National School Lunch Extended Summer Lunch Program. This is the free lunch program that provided free lunches during the school closure during the last school year.

This means that ALL students at IGS will receive free breakfast and lunch every day from September 1 through December 18th!

If you have any lunch bills from the beginning of school through September 1st, you will still need to pay those. If you receive a bill with any amount on it, that means you owe that amount . But from now until the end of December, all breakfast and lunch will be free for all students!

If you have any questions, please call the office.
#GoPirates!

Iuka Lady Pirates are 1-1 on the season and face Cisne at home on Monday August 31st.

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT FOR ALL REMOTE LEARNING STUDENTS AND PARENTS:

Reminder that we will have a material pickup for all remote learners on Thursday, Aug. 20 from 12:30 - 3:30PM. All materials will need to be picked up during these hours. No appointment is necessary. You must wear a mask and enter door #1 to have a temperature scan, before you enter the building. You must report only to the main office.

We will also be offering sack lunches for all remote learners. Pickup of sack lunches will be on Mondays and Wednesdays from 10:30 - 11:00AM. If you plan on participating in the lunch program, you must notify the office when you come pickup materials. This is NOT a free lunch program, unless you already qualify for the school's free/reduced lunch program. If you choose to participate, you will be billed for lunches each week.

If you have any questions, please call the office at 323-6233.

CLARIFICATION FOR PARENTS

The public hearing scheduled for Monday, August 17th is NOT an informational meeting concerning Remote Learning. This hearing is an open forum to allow the public to make comments about the proposed remote learning plan that has to be approved for us to provide remote learning.

Information about how the Remote Learning Plan works, as well as, how to get materials for your child who is remote learning, will be released soon.

Again, you do not have to be at this hearing in order for your child to be in remote learning.

Original Post

Notice is hereby given that the Iuka Grade School District #7 Board of Education will conduct a public hearing to be held on Monday, August 17th, 2020 at 7:00. in the Iuka Grade School Library. The purpose of the public hearing is to satisfy the legal requirements prior to approval of a Remote Learning Day Program to be implemented in conjunction with or in lieu of the use of Emergency Days.

Brian Hancock
Secretary of the Board of Education
Iuka Comm. Cons. Dist. #7

post_text:
Face Mask Guidance

All students and staff members will be required to wear a face masks while on the bus and inside the building. We encourage parents to supply their child with multiple face masks to ensure they wear a clean one everyday and allow for a mask that is comfortable for them.

Students will be allowed to wear a hat or headband with buttons to keep straps off of their ears. They will also be allowed to wear gaiters as long as they cover both the mouth and nose.

Please remember that all face masks must be multiple layered to ensure maximum protection.

If you have any questions, please call the office. 323-6233

post_text:
COVID-19 Return to School Policies and Procedures

We have attached the policies and procedures flyer to this post concerning Return to School during the COVID-19 Pandemic.

Please understand, these procedures are based on guidelines handed down from the Illinois State Board of Education and the Illinois Department of Health.

We understand that not all of the guidelines will be easy to follow or even favorable, however, we want to do everything we can to make sure your children are safe. We feel that it is imperative for students to get back to school and begin flourishing again.

We appreciate your support in keeping your children and our school safe!

Mr. Consolino

Cindy Collier Burkett
June 24 at 5:49 PM ·

Yes, I would say he looks happy! My son, Levi Burkett, recently completed his training/orientation for the State Department. He received his first assignment.. Guangzhou, China! as an embassy ambassador, working in immigration law. China was his first choice and needless to say he was surprised and obviously thrilled! He will now move onto Washington, DC for language training. Will probably be in the states until at least next spring. We sure are proud of him!!

post_text:
This is our official last week of school. The last day of remote learning will be Wednesday, May 20.

On Thursday, May 21 and Friday May 22 we will be having our last work drop off for the school year. When you drop off your work, you will be given your students' end of the year awards and personal belongings from their lockers and desks. Students whose last names begin with letters A-M will come on May 21. Students whose last names begin with letters N-Z will come on May 22nd.

Students are reminded that all library books will need to be returned on May 21 and 22.

Volleyball players are reminded that their uniforms should also be returned on May 21 and 22.

8th Grade Graduation will be held on Thursday, May 21st. This year's ceremony will be limited to the 8th grade students and their parents. You can listen to the ceremony, if you are within the village limits, on 87.7FM. You will also be able to watch from home via livestream on the school's facebook page.

If you have any questions, please call the office.

Calling on Pirate Family!

We found out today that one of our Pirate families had a fire and they have had to move into a hotel. They lost a lot of their personal belongings and really need our help. We have listed sizes for clothes for both adults and the one child in the family below. If you are able to help with any clothing items, please bag them up (please wash) and set them by the front door of the school. One of the school personnel will make sure they get to the family! Thanks in advance for all your help! If you have any questions, please direct message our FB page or call the school on Monday. 323-6233

post_text:
8th Grade Graduation Information

Broadcasts: 87.7FM
Livestream on IGS Facebook Page

Students should arrive, in cap and gowns, between 5:40 and 5:50PM. Tune your radio to 87.7FM to listen to the ceremony. We will also Livestream the video of speeches and award announcements on the IGS Facebook Page.

Students and parents should remain in their cars.

Each student will have one parking spot reserved by a sign with their name on it. These signs are yours to keep and take with you . Please put it in your car when you arrive.
We will begin the ceremony at approximately 6:00.

All students and parents will be remain in their cars until directed to approach the building.

If you have any questions, call the office at 323-6233.

8th Grade Graduation Information

Livestream on IGS Facebook Page

Students should arrive, in cap and gowns, between 5:40 and 5:50PM. Tune your radio to 87.7FM to listen to the ceremony. We will also Livestream the video of speeches and award announcements on the IGS Facebook Page.

Students and parents should remain in their cars.

Each student will have one parking spot reserved by a sign with their name on it. These signs are yours to keep and take with you . Please put it in your car when you arrive.
We will begin the ceremony at approximately 6:00.

All students and parents will be remain in their cars until directed to approach the building.

If you have any questions, call the office at 323-6233.

Reminders:

We will have a work pickup and dropoff again this Monday, May 4th from 9:00am to 1:00pm. Please remember to only send one person to the front of the building to exchange work.

Parents and students are reminded that it is very important to continue to complete work as we make our push towards the end of the year. All work turned in will be graded. Any work not turned in will be counted as incomplete. Wednesday, May 20th will be the last day of Remote Learning.

Thursday, May 21st and Friday, May 22nd from 9:00am to 1:00pm will be the final two days to turn in work and pickup personal belongings at the school. Students whose last names begin with letters A-M will pickup on May 21st, and students whose last names begin with N-Z will pickup on May 22nd.

Students are reminded that all school books, including library books, must be returned by May 21st. Junior High Students are asked to return all books on Monday, May 4.

post_text:
If your family has experienced a change in job status due to Covid-19 closures or reductions in hours, it may affect your free/reduced lunch status for the school. If either parent has lost their job or have suffered a reduction in hours that has affected your monthly income, you may now be considered free or reduced for school lunches. This may help you qualify for financial support from the state of Illinois, as well. If you believe that this may affect you, please call the office to make arrangements to fill out the necessary paperwork as soon as possible.

This does not affect, in any way, the free lunches being provided to all students during the closure.

We are encouraging parents to bring their students, but please only let one person come up to the building to exchange work. If you are a lunch pickup person, please come from 11:30 - 12:00 as usual.

Remember, Jr. High students will only need to come if they have requested work on paper, otherwise, they need to be checking Google Classroom each day for their work.

Any work not picked up on Monday will be delivered to mailboxes or doorsteps on Tuesday.

If you have any questions, please call the office on Monday.

post_text:
The Governor announced yesterday that the school closure has been extended through April 30, 2020. This means that the tentative return to school date will be Friday, May 1st.

We will have a work dropoff and pickup of new work for Remote Learning Days on Monday, April 13 from 9am to 1pm. All work will be dropped off in tubs at the front of the building. New work packets will be picked up at the same time. We ask that you send one person to the front of the building to exchange work. If you are unable to pickup work on Monday, we will be making deliveries to homes on Tuesday, April 14.

It is very important for all students to complete their Remote Learning Day activities. The work completed at home can positively affect your end of the year grades for classes. Jr. High students are reminded that they need to be logging into google classroom each day to complete those online assignments.

If you have any questions, please call the school office at 323-6233.

If you have any questions, please call the school office at 323-6233.

Governor Pritzker has extended the school closure through Tuesday, April 7th. No decision has been made yet to determine what the exact date of return to school will be for Iuka Grade School. A decision will be made at a later time.

Lunch distribution will continue with one change. We will only be distributing lunches on Mondays and Wednesdays in order to better limit social contact. We will still be providing lunch and breakfast for the entire week. We will pass out Monday/Tuesday sacks on Monday and Wednesday/Thursday/Friday sacks on Wednesday. Pickup will still be between 11:30 and 12:00 each Monday and Wednesday.

There will be no further attendance messages. Please encourage your children to keep up with their Remote Learning Assignments so they will be ready to turn in when we return to school.

Please remember that teachers will be responding to emails concerning remote learning assignments between 9am and 12pm each day. You are welcome to send emails after these hours, however, teachers may not be able respond until the following day.

If you have any questions, please call the school at 323-6233.

post_text:
We will have one change to the lunch pickup instructions. Instead of lunches being delivered to your car, we ask that you have one person from your vehicle come up and pick up the number of lunches you need. Lunches will be sitting out on a table. Please only take the number of lunches that you have requested. Lunch pickup will be school days during the closing, from 11:30 – 12:00 each day.

If your child missed school on Monday, work packets will also be sitting on a table, clearly marked with your child’s name, and can be picked up any school day from 11:30 – 12:00.

Please remember that the school will be closed from Tuesday, March 17 through Monday, March 30. We are scheduled to return to school on Tuesday, March 31st.

You can call the office anytime to request to be added to the lunch pickup list at 323-6233.

Iuka Grade School will be enacting our Remote Learning Day Plan for students during the school closure. This will allow students to continue to have meaningful work while they are at home to continue the learning process. Students will be provided with learning packets and/or electronic assignments on Monday. Teachers will be available each day from 9:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. via email to answer questions, if needed.

You will also receive an automated call each day during the closure to "take attendance" for your child. You will only need to press "1" to count your child as present for Remote Learning. This will allow us to continue to provide learning and services, like lunches and breakfasts, during the closure.

All extra curricular activities at the school have been cancelled, including the volleyball game on Monday. We apologize to the families in Iuka for any undo hardship this closing has on you. More information will be shared as it becomes available.

post_text:
Volleyball season is quickly approaching and we are now looking for volunteers to help with the concession stand for game nights.

This year, we are sending out the list of scheduled home games for basketball and asking all of our great parents, family, and staff members to sign up to help work the concession stand. Our concession stand directly helps with the purchase of equipment and uniforms for Baseball, Basketball, Volleyball, Band, Color Guard, and Track. So please, sign up for a few dates, in order to help the Pirate Backers!

Below is a list of all of the available dates for Volleyball games for the season. Please mark the box next to the game or games that you can work, and a member of the Pirate Backers will call you the week of the game to remind you. If everyone signs up for a few games, we will have more than enough help! After we have received all requests for dates, parents will be assigned nights according to availability. Please return this note with your selected dates by Friday, January 24th to get the dates you want!

The class that collected the most items, with 555, was Mrs. Wilzbach's Kindergarten Class! They enjoyed a doughnut party this morning as their reward!

#GoPirates!

post_text:
All students PK – 5th grade will be allowed to dress in costume for the Halloween Parade and Parties on Friday, November 1, 2019. All students are asked to come to school in costume, ready for the parties. We ask that parents use discretion in the taste of our students’ costumes. No costumes depicting bodily injuries, simulated blood, bleeding, or bloody clothes will be permitted. Students will not be allowed to have weapons, of any type (toy guns, toy knives, etc.), as part of their costumes. Hair color and hair glitter will be permitted on this day only as part of a costume for grades PK – 5th. Students in grades 6th – 8th will not participate by dressing in costumes and must follow all dress code rules, including hair coloring and hair glitter. However, this will be Red Ribbon Week, so all Jr. High Students are encouraged to dress in Halloween colors (orange, black, purple). If you have any questions concerning this matter feel free to call the school.

Parade Begins 10:15 AM
Parties Begin 10:45 AM
Dismissal 11:30 AM
